<BaseLayout title="Basic Training Settings Explained" description="Understand basic LoRA training settings such as steps, repeats, learning rate, and resolution." canonicalPath="/lora/training-settings/"><article class="content-section article-body"><h1>Basic Training Settings Explained</h1><p>Training settings control how quickly and strongly the LoRA learns. Learning rate, repeats, steps, resolution, and network size should be adjusted gradually.</p><p>Keep a run log. Record dataset version, caption style, settings, and test prompts so you can compare results instead of guessing what changed.</p></article></BaseLayout>
